		<div>Flordiel minitrees have a &quot;long range stun&quot; that ignores your runes.<br />
So do the Magehunter/Magekiller on Island of Madness.<br />
<br />
The best part about these ? No range.<br />
I've been stunned at 45+ range.<br />
<br />
Anyway about the lady, it happens a LOT..<br />
Mayor Tressam's Snare/DoT or DoT, her DoT  the list is just too long.<br />
<br />
<br />
Edit : BTW something i dont think everyone knows....<br />
<br />
There are 4 types of attacks.<br />
<br />
A) Auto-attack : These are the basic melee, and are not affected by runes at all<br />
Also they are not affected by &quot;silence&quot; since they are not &quot;casted&quot;.<br />
<br />
B) Special Attacks : I expect these to be reflected by runes <br />
These cost endurance for players, and are considered as spells (cant use when silenced)<br />
<br />
C) Procs : They can come from Auto-attack or specials.<br />
I know reflect works on them, because Old Targonor skeletons can be stunned for 18sec by runes.<br />
This spell is cast only when in melee, and only when attacked, i expect this to be a &quot;1 charge proc buff&quot;.<br />
<br />
D) Casted Spells : No comment<br />
<br />
<br />
So depending on what type off attack, runes should act differently.<br />
I am still curious about how archery works...<br />
But with the unreliability of runes, you cant know.<br />
<br />
However since melees cant use &quot;specials&quot; when silenced, these specials are considered as &quot;spells&quot;.<br />
So Runes should protect us.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
