		<div>Few things I wanna say after reading through this thread again.<br />
<br />
I like spells to have pros and cons, it's about having to make choices and value situations, not having everything be good at all times which it seems most people here would prefer. That would only make it more dull, in my opinion. For example the range thing on Flamespear is something you gotta consider before using it, no it's not gonna be good 2 feet from the mob. This spell is a good opener, but that's it, and the way it should be used, again imo. <br />
<br />
A lot of complaints here also on Seradon's star nuke, and I agree with these comments and I'm not sure what this spell is supposed to bring that we didn't have already, other than that it's cold based. <br />
<br />
Also to comment a bit on Emilia's comparison with his Rogue mate, I wouldn't look as much on what other classes have and don't have, but this is just my attitude to playing these games and class balance... Playing a rogue is a very different experience than playing a sorceror, just go with whatever class you're having the most fun with. If the rogue has higher DPS in short fights? Good for him! I'd look for a rogue when I set up groups!<br />
<br />
Last I think sorcerors are in fairly good shape, but there's a few tweaks I'd like to see:<br />
<br />
-All bugs regarding timers, wards and counters must be fixed!<br />
-Forget line needs looked at, this spell appears to do nothing. <br />
-Insight buff castable on others.<br />
-I'd still like to see a 60 or 90 sec DoT for sorcerors, just enough to be worth casting during long fights, also with upcoming raid encounters in mind.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
